<div class="row">
	<div id="get-invovled">
		<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-xs-12">
			<div class="pad-all">
				<img class="img-responsive" src="http://placehold.it/200/200">
				<h3 class="text-uppercase text-center">Hike Sipi Falls</h3>
				<p class="text-block">Mount Elgon and Sipi Falls are a breath of fresh air from the hard work of volunteering. At 4,321m, Mount Elgon is the eight highest mountain in Africa and a paradise for trekkers and outdoor enthusiasts. As well as multi-night expeditions there are short hikes around the local area where you will see stunning waterfalls and swim in plunge pools. There is plenty of wildlife too and bird lovers should bring their binoculars.</p>
				<p>If you're looking to relax you can enjoy amazing food, coffee and wine.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-xs-12">
			<div class="pad-all">
				<img class="img-responsive" src="http://placehold.it/200/200">
				<h3 class="text-uppercase text-center">Raft the Nile</h3>
				<p class="text-block">A trip to Uganda is not complete without having rafted the source of the Nile. This legendary river is the longest in the world and flows through eleven countries past the historic ancient sites in Egypt and out into the Mediterranean sea. In Uganda the White Nile is rough, wide and bordered on both sides by lush green vegetation. Its white water is truly incredible and when your raft flips and you are pulled through its deep rapids you can ponder the epic journey the water around you will make. You however should pop up a few metres downstream feeling like you have truly earned a Nile Special, the local beer.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-xs-12">
			<div class="pad-all">
				<img class="img-responsive" src="http://placehold.it/200/200">
				<h3 class="text-uppercase text-center">Adventure Safari</h3>
				<p class="text-block">Uganda is blessed with fantastic wildlife and highlights include Queen Elizabeth National Park and the frankly fantastically named Bwindi Impenetrable Forest. QENP is one of the most biodiverse national parks in the world, and you can see tree climbing lions, hippos, leopards, hippos and chimpanzees to name a few and over 600 bird species. There is a range of accommodation from the fairly budget to the ultra-luxurious if you are looking to unwind after a job well done. Bwindi Impenetrable Forest is a UNESCO world heritage site home to roughly half of the world's gorilla population.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-xs-12">
			<div class="pad-all">
				<img class="img-responsive" src="http://placehold.it/200/200">
				<h3 class="text-uppercase text-center">Lake Victoria</h3>
				<p class="text-block">The Ssese Islands are an archipelago of eighty-four islands in the northwestern part of Lake Victoria in Uganda. A number of islands have fantastic beaches and luxury lodges providing you with the perfect setting to unwind at the end of your trip.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		 <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-xs-12">
			<div class="pad-all">
				<img class="img-responsive" src="http://placehold.it/200/200">
				<h3 class="text-uppercase text-center">Equator</h3>
				<p class="text-block">If you have ever wanted to have a foot in each of the Northern and Southern Hemispheres, Uganda is the place to cross that off your bucket list. You can also watch water drain clockwise and anti-clockwise and then buy a t-shirt to remember your momentous day.</p>
			</div>
